    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc id="hl0501002" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>STEERING WHEEL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-seat the retainer with slip ring on the back of the steering wheel and install the
                    three pan head screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the steering wheel on the steering column shaft, being careful to align the match
                    mark on the steering wheel with the mark on the steering shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501006">Figure 6</hotlnk>). Install the steering wheel nut and tighten as
                    specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s05010t_19.xml" xrefid="hl0501001">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0501001"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501006" filename="../figg05/G0501006.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Steering Column Shaft Alignment Mark</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the horn button by centering it on the steering wheel and pushing it firmly into
                    place.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
